args:
It turns out Loki was the driving force behind
Satan's revival. Betrayed by him, Origa merges
with Satan and destroys Grams. The angels and
apostles fight back, but in the end they win only
a brief respiteâ€”one that comes at the cost of
the angels' lives.
The true mastermind behind Satan's\nrebirth was Loki, the demon who has\nbeen impersonating Harle.
He sealed the real Harle away in another\nworld years ago, and has been using his\nlikeness ever since.

Okay, hold on. So every time that smug
jerk got in our way these past few years,
it was actually some demon who was
PRETENDING to be him?!
Correct. And the ones who conspired with\nLoki to resurrect Satan were the traitor\napostle Basileus, as well as...
Ha ha ha! Wonderful! Truly wonderful!\nThis day is finally here!
Satan's glorious rebirth is upon us!
At last, I have the power to fight back\nagainst the Progenitor's designs.
Why are you doing this, Origa?!\nAnd who or what is the Progenitor?!
One of this world's two creators from long\nbefore the Goddess's timeâ€”and one who\nwill soon return from another world.
He means to remake our world into a\nbleak and hollow place devoid of any\npossibility for happiness.
I will not let such a thing come to pass.\nThe Progenitor will fall by my hand!
Then Satan holds the power to resist the\nProgenitor? The Sacred Tree told it\nquite differently.
We heard the only force that might rival\nthe Progenitor was Bahamutâ€”the Origin.
It seems she was deceived,\nas was Basileus.
Is her mind being corrupted\nby Satan's miasma?
That's absurd! The Auspex's holy mana\nshould grant her control over Satan!
What's absurd is a lowly human imagining\nthey could bridle the Demonlord.
Damn you, Loki! You tricked us!
But...why?! You spoke with such passion...\nabout thwarting the Progenitor's designs!
Oh, I'm no more a fan of the world he\naims to make than you areâ€”but I also\nhave no intention of defending this one.

I'm a simple demon who lives for the
pleasure of the moment. My goal was to
revive my lord. In fact, I only ever had one
reason for approaching you in particular...
I wanted to see the Auspex hang all her\nhopes on the Demonlord's power only\nto destroy all she sought to protect!
The Auspex's consciousness has been\nswallowed up by Satan.

Hark, the end is nigh! Now, my lord!
Let us indulge in delightful destruction!
Let all which lives become a sacrifice
offered unto your glorious form!
Oooo! Has the icy schemer finally lost his\ncool? What a very rare thing...and what\nan utterly transparent ploy.
Did you really think I would let you take\nMetatron's Sacred Shard?\nIf you're going to be like that, then...
Heh heh heh. I've placed it in my lord's\ncare. If you succeed in taking it, I'll give\nyou a lovely prize.
You would do well not to underestimate\nme. I'll clean up the mess I've made.\nSatan will not have this world.
You...you would all still support me?
Although I have an extensive list of\ncomplaints regarding your recent actions,\nwe presently share a common goal.
We can chew you out once this is over.\nFor now, we're on the same side.
Satan was sealed away by that Shard,\nso we'll need it if we hope to do so again.
You heard the man, folks. Time for a\nrousing game of Snatch That Shard!
An ant may as well attempt to seize a\ncastle...but I wish you the best of luck.

Ending things all at once is no fun at all,
my lord. If you kill them one by one,
you can revel as each new death breeds
further terror and despair.
I'm only glad...you're all right...\nMy son...
And I'm afraid he didn't buy Basileus\nmuch time; an apostle can't last a day\nwith a severed Sigil.

Well, that was quite the dramatic surprise!
But I fear we're not looking for any
tearjerker scenes in this particular drama.
The Demonlord craves only despair.
Aaaand now it seems you've bored him.\nTime to move on to the next amusement!\nAaaah ha ha ha ha!
What do they plan to do out there?!
Look there! Is that a fiend?!
Dearest citizens of Grams! Pray permit me\nto present you all with a lovely gift from\nthe Demonlord himself! Please do enjoy.
Let us have a game, my dear apostles!\nWhile my lord crushes the city underfoot,\nyou can attempt to save its people!
I'll give you one point for each person you\nmanage to save from a horrible death.\nAaaaah ha ha ha ha!
Satan flooded the area with miasma,\ncausing frenzied fiends to attack and\nplunging Grams into utter chaos.
We held them back as best we could to\nsave those still standing, and that alone\ntook everything we had.

Ooo, you're getting a bit sloppy there.
Distracted by the loss of your friend?
But I thought he was just another tool
in your quest for revenge!
It's no use, you know. You're no match for\nmy lord in that stateâ€”or any state, really.
Did we lose him too? I can't see\nanything through these flames!
Oh dear. Bored of crushing their little\nhopes already, my lord? Well then,\nI suppose the game ends here.
He's gathering energy in the skyâ€”\nenough to leave all of Grams in ashes!
We can't reach him up there!
But the city's still full of people!\nWhat do we do?!
We angels will intercept his attack in\nmidair. Doing so should lessen the\ndamage on the ground.
It is the only option available if we want\nto keep these people alive.
Then we'll think of something else!
There's no time to argue.\nHe's ready to fire.
We'll stop his attackâ€”the rest of you\njust focus on keeping the citizens safe.
Have faith, all of you; we have no intention\nof going to our death this day.
She's right. I hate it, but she's right.\nAll we can do now is believe in them.
Then if we are all ready?

You would engage in a test of strength
against the Demonlord? What hubris!
In that case, let your foolish pride be
shattered with your pathetic bodies.
Keep going! We have to find a way!
Our children are counting on us!
The angels! Where are the angels?!
Well...that was a hell of a thing...
What sort of example...am I setting...?\nThis is...a clear failure...
No... I can't leave...before my son...
Oh, Little Pi... I'm so...sorry, sweetie...
Well, shut the drawbridge! I didn't think\nthose angels had it in them to blunt my\nlord's attack.

But yeeesh, they do NOT look to be in very
good shape. Oh, well! The next blow is
going to wipe out the city anyway, sooo...
Now, my lord! Deliver your final judgment!

(Hmm. The Demonlord's response is faint.
It seems he spent more strength than I
imagined eradicating those angels...
My, but the surprises just keep coming!)
In that case, my lord, it's time for you to\ntake a much-earned rest swaddled in a\ncozy blanket of miasma.

I have granted life on this planet a few
final days of respite, so I encourage you
all to spend it wisely. See the sights!
Maybe try a new restaurant or two.
For the more beautiful and poignant these\nfew final memories of life are, the greater\nyour despair at the inevitable end will be!
...So we only have a few days at best\nbefore Satan awakens?
Leaving the time period vague to heighten\nour anxiety was an especially vile choice.
All this happened half a day agoâ€”shortly\nbefore you all arrived.
But you apostles are connected to the\nangels through those Sigils dealies, right?\nSo if they die...
Then we will follow within a day's time.\nWhich means we're all basically ghosts\nat this point, which is fun.
There must be something we can do!
The connections are severedâ€”we can all\nfeel it. The angels are not coming back.
There has never been a case of an apostle\nsurviving a severed Sigil. There's no\ngetting out of this one.
It's not so bad, actually. I mean, we've all\nbeen prepared for this moment ever since\nwe became apostles.

And if death is gonna grab us in his bony
hand and squeeze, we're just gonna have
to go out with a bang. That's how apostles
do it.
All right, that's enough gloom and doom.\nLet's get back to work.
Great job with the explanation, Pinon.\nThat earned you some candy.
Nevin, am I a heartless person? I mean,\nGabriel is dead, and yet I'm forcing myself\nnot to grieve or even really think about it.

That's because she raised you right.
Look, I'll be honestâ€”I'm white-knuckling
my way through this thing too. But I can't
go disappointing Ramiel at the end.
We're all in the same boat here, trust me.\nSo just keep your eyes forward and fight\nlike a bastard to your very last breath.
I will! Er, but are you certain we shouldn't\ntell the prince about Harle?
He said it himself when the Halidom\ncavalry arrived...
With that impostor hiding in the miasma,\nI doubt they'd believe me if I tried to\nconvince them I'm the genuine article.
No sense adding to the chaos. I'll just work\nsolo for a bit and wait for the right time to\nbreak the good news of my return.

It sounded like he was looking into a way
through the miasma. I tell ya, that guy
wants revenge on Loki like a ham
sandwich wants some good mustard.
Bad news, folks! We've just spotted\nan army marching on the city!
Sounds like a neighboring country who had\nan emissary killed at the Auspecalia. They\nmean to enter the miasma and avenge him.
Don't they know what that stuff\nwill do to them?
Oh, I told 'emâ€”they just don't care.\nThey're dead set on getting revenge\nagainst Satan, no matter what.
Pinon, run and tell the prince about this.\nWe've got a mass suicide to stop.
